```json
{
"application": "Slurm",
"software": [
"bcftools@1.12",
"spack@0.17.3",
"gcc@10.2.0",
"gsl@2.7",
"htslib@1.12",
"py-matplotlib@3.4.3",
"samtools@1.13"
],
"resources": [
"slurm",
"spack",
"gcc",
"gsl",
"htslib",
"py-matplotlib",
"samtools",
"32G",
"16 cores"
]
}
```

This script is running on the Slurm workload manager. It uses the Spack package manager to install `bcftools` version 1.12, with dependencies including `gsl`, `htslib`, and `py-matplotlib`. The script also uses the `gcc` compiler version 10.2.0. 

It requires 32GB of memory, 16 CPU cores, and runs for a maximum of 48 hours. The script also uses the `slurm` module and sets up the Spack environment. Finally, it attempts to install `samtools` version 1.13 as a follow-up job after `bcftools` is installed.
